"6:35:28" : {s: 6, a: 35, w: 28, r: "جهل", t: "ٱلْجَٰهِلِينَ", l: "جَاهِل", lc: 10, tl: "l-jāhilīna", lb: "অজ্ঞ",e: "the ignorant", b: "মূর্খদের", i: "orang-orang yang jahil", f: 6, rm: "To be ignorant, not know of a thing, to be silly or foolish, boil vehemently, pretend ignorance, feign ignorance, reckon or esteem someone, cause commotion or unsteadiness, display wrong conduct, to be void of knowledge, believe a thing to be different from what it is in reality, do a thing in a manner different from that in which it ought to be done, proceed without knowledge, to ignore a thing, to be pagan."},
